text: Several vessels in the 19th century were named Sincapore, a contemporary variant of the name Singapore: *Sincapore, a brig first mentioned in Lloyd's List in 1821, that wrecked at Algoa Bay in 1824. * was launched in New Brunswick and wrecked at Table Bay in 1830. *Sincapore was a steam-ship operating in Asian waters in 1854. title: Sincapore (ship)
